<TITLE> RMG worker dies, road blocked </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 13 (bdnews24.com)  Readymade garment workers blocked the busy Rokeya Sarani road in the capital for about half an hour on Thursday after a co-worker died in a road accident, the police said. Renu Akhtar, 35, was going to Vision Garments, her workplace, in Mirpur-14. Sub-Inspector of Mirpur Police Station Taj Nahar told bdnews24.com, "Renu died on the spot at 11:30am while crossing the road under a footbridge as a bus of Badda-Mirpur route ran over her." The news spread quickly among fellow garment workers and over 100 workers came out into the streets and laid a siege to the road. As the police seized the bus and arrested its driver Shamim, the workers lifted the siege. bd
